WEBVTT

00:06.966 --> 00:09.298
(theme music playing )

00:17.727 --> 00:20.639
( crowd chanting )
Spartacus! Spartacus! Spartacus!

00:27.236 --> 00:29.522
( crowd continues chanting )

00:34.994 --> 00:36.985
They roar your name.

00:38.748 --> 00:41.706
Soon they shall roar
yours as well

00:41.876 --> 00:45.289
or mourn it,
if your mind is absent the task.

00:46.672 --> 00:48.628
l'm yet to have word
on my wife and son.

00:48.799 --> 00:51.506
I will not fight alongside a man
who is not clear to his purpose.

00:53.137 --> 00:55.503
I am clear.

00:55.681 --> 00:58.718
My purpose is blood.

01:30.883 --> 01:32.544
Shield.

01:35.137 --> 01:38.220
(yelling)

01:51.487 --> 01:52.693
Oh yes!

01:52.863 --> 01:55.479
Even chained to an inferior gladiator,
Spartacus prevails.

01:55.658 --> 01:58.525
One would expect no less
from the champion of Capua.

01:58.703 --> 02:01.319
See how he ignites
the crowd.

02:01.497 --> 02:03.328
His presence
at your son's birthday

02:03.499 --> 02:05.285
will be the talk
of the republic.

02:05.459 --> 02:07.871
A far cry
from my own 15th year.

02:08.045 --> 02:10.422
When I put on the toga virilis
and passed into manhood,

02:10.589 --> 02:13.922
it was a stuffy, formal ceremony
ridden with corpses and hags.

02:14.093 --> 02:17.460
Batiatus: My father
deemed himself an orator,

02:17.638 --> 02:20.926
lulled our guests to slumber,
some never to reawaken.

02:21.100 --> 02:22.761
We would not have it so
for Numerius.

02:22.935 --> 02:25.176
Calavius: He's been clamoring
for a pair of your finest

02:25.354 --> 02:27.936
to battle in exhibition
at his celebration.

02:28.107 --> 02:29.813
Well, we would see him
well satisfied.

02:29.984 --> 02:31.849
And by extension,
his noble father.

02:32.028 --> 02:34.485
Though a thought strikes--
if you hold the celebration

02:34.655 --> 02:36.191
beneath my humble roof,

02:36.365 --> 02:38.947
then your boy can bear close witness
to all my gladiators.

02:39.118 --> 02:42.485
Could we, Father? Please?

02:42.663 --> 02:46.121
And the extra cost
for such generosity?

02:46.292 --> 02:48.328
A favor between friends.

02:48.502 --> 02:51.289
Received with much gratitude.

02:54.133 --> 02:57.466
You're next, Spartacus.

02:59.972 --> 03:01.712
Come here.

03:13.152 --> 03:15.484
Are you certain
it won't cause imposition?

03:15.654 --> 03:17.815
Place it
from your thoughts.

03:17.990 --> 03:20.276
A boy becomes a man
but once in his life.

03:20.451 --> 03:22.658
He should be richly indulged
in his interests.

03:22.828 --> 03:26.491
He never ceases
to tire of the games.

03:26.665 --> 03:28.826
He's of the same obsessive ilk
as llithyia

03:29.001 --> 03:30.912
regarding blood and sport.

03:31.087 --> 03:33.749
Herabsence
comes as a surprise.

03:33.923 --> 03:35.879
Has she returned to Rome,

03:36.050 --> 03:37.881
absent farewells?

03:38.052 --> 03:39.258
No.

03:39.428 --> 03:41.339
She has been feeling unwell.

03:42.640 --> 03:43.971
Nothing serious, I hope?

03:44.141 --> 03:47.008
It will pass, as all things
born of a weak stomach.

04:10.042 --> 04:12.499
His armor gives pause.

04:12.670 --> 04:14.706
Then we shall aim higher.

04:27.768 --> 04:29.383
Pull!

04:48.247 --> 04:49.612
Oh.

04:49.790 --> 04:51.576
Oh yeah!

05:12.146 --> 05:13.761
I've never seen
anything like it.

05:25.784 --> 05:29.993
( crowd chanting )

05:30.164 --> 05:31.654
Yeah!

05:36.295 --> 05:39.253
Man: Open the gates!
Open the gates!

05:39.423 --> 05:41.129
Get up.

05:41.300 --> 05:43.712
( men cheering )

05:43.886 --> 05:45.877
Man: Spartacus.

05:48.098 --> 05:50.714
Man: Live to fight
another day.

05:54.563 --> 05:56.975
lt pains me to watch others
claim your laurels.

05:57.149 --> 06:00.983
Your pain will increase
if you continue to stand beside me.

06:03.656 --> 06:06.523
Man: Well done, brother.

06:06.700 --> 06:08.486
Well done.

06:11.664 --> 06:13.996
- You fought well today.
- The gods favored me

06:14.166 --> 06:15.542
to count you as ally.

06:15.709 --> 06:17.961
Their favor extends
beyond the arena.

06:20.714 --> 06:22.375
Aurelia.

06:34.520 --> 06:37.353
lfeared lwould never
hold you again.

06:37.523 --> 06:40.765
Ashur said he found only blood
when I sent him to you with message.

06:40.943 --> 06:43.355
- Titus had returned.
- Did he hurt you?

06:43.529 --> 06:45.645
I will see his heart
from his fucking chest.

06:45.823 --> 06:48.109
The blood was not mine.

06:48.284 --> 06:51.822
I cut him, deep and low.

06:51.996 --> 06:56.740
He will never force himself
on a woman again.

06:56.917 --> 06:59.875
Afterwards I sought refuge
with my brother's family in the hills.

07:00.045 --> 07:02.331
The slave girl found me there,

07:02.506 --> 07:04.497
by Spartacus's direction.

07:04.675 --> 07:06.666
Thank the gods you're safe.

07:11.265 --> 07:15.349
Where were they when Titus
first laid hands on me?

07:15.519 --> 07:18.056
I still carry his child.

07:22.067 --> 07:25.355
Nothing's changed, Varro.

07:25.529 --> 07:28.646
The entire world has changed,

07:28.824 --> 07:31.736
and I along with it.

07:31.910 --> 07:33.946
The child--

07:34.121 --> 07:36.032
it springs from your belly,

07:36.206 --> 07:37.742
a part of you.

07:37.916 --> 07:40.248
And I would love it as such

07:40.419 --> 07:42.410
if you would have it so.

07:56.435 --> 07:58.801
(Licinia laughing)

08:08.947 --> 08:11.324
Your absence was noticed.

08:11.492 --> 08:13.778
Absence?

08:13.952 --> 08:15.488
The games.

08:15.663 --> 08:18.075
You were supposed to join us.

08:18.248 --> 08:20.955
I could not face prying eyes.

08:21.126 --> 08:24.539
One look into mine and they
would have full knowledge--

08:24.713 --> 08:27.125
Licinia's blood,

08:27.299 --> 08:30.336
her skull steeped
between my fingers.

08:30.511 --> 08:34.971
Jupiter's cock,
would you come to grips?

08:35.140 --> 08:37.552
Licinia's murder
and your part in it

08:37.726 --> 08:39.262
have been concealed.

08:39.436 --> 08:43.020
The truth will only unfold

08:43.190 --> 08:45.932
if yourjaw splits
and your tongue unfurls in song.

08:46.110 --> 08:47.441
What would you
have me do?

08:47.611 --> 08:49.977
Appear yourself,

08:50.155 --> 08:54.319
absent conscience
of deeds unknown.

08:54.493 --> 08:57.326
The magistrate's celebration
provides a perfect opportunity.

08:57.496 --> 08:59.657
The venue turns
to my husband as host.

08:59.832 --> 09:01.788
You won't even have to
move from under this roof,

09:01.959 --> 09:04.666
my hand ever present
to steady your resolve.

09:05.671 --> 09:08.162
You will guide me
through this?

09:09.842 --> 09:12.504
As trusted friend.

09:12.678 --> 09:15.294
And as such,
I require a favor.

09:16.348 --> 09:18.805
We would swell
the ranks of celebration

09:18.976 --> 09:21.843
with these noble citizens,

09:22.020 --> 09:24.602
ones I'm certain
would accept the invite

09:24.773 --> 09:27.856
from the daughter
of Senator Albinius.

09:31.280 --> 09:33.316
Gather yourself.

09:34.742 --> 09:36.733
See it done.

10:02.936 --> 10:04.801
( groans )

10:04.980 --> 10:08.313
I owe you more
than I can ever repay.

10:08.484 --> 10:10.816
If you had not sent Mira
to find my wife...

10:10.986 --> 10:12.772
She has taken you
backthen?

10:12.946 --> 10:15.323
And lwill yet be
the man she deserves.

10:15.491 --> 10:18.107
If not, I shall remind you
of your shortcomings.

10:18.285 --> 10:21.277
Oh, it lifts the heart

10:21.455 --> 10:24.697
to see a man reunited
with his woman.

10:24.875 --> 10:28.288
Now you'll have someone
to weep for you when you die.

10:28.462 --> 10:30.748
If I fall,
it will be in the arena,

10:30.923 --> 10:33.084
as a gladiator.

10:33.258 --> 10:35.670
You remember what that is like,
do you not?

10:38.138 --> 10:39.719
Spartacus, Crixus,

10:39.890 --> 10:41.755
you are summoned.

10:42.893 --> 10:45.009
We are to fight each other?

10:45.187 --> 10:46.893
Numerius has chosen.

10:47.064 --> 10:48.929
He insisted on drinking in
the spectacle

10:49.107 --> 10:51.769
of present glories
pitted against the past.

10:51.944 --> 10:54.560
And his thirst shall be
satisfied, Dominus.

10:54.738 --> 10:56.239
Keep in mind
this is an exhibition.

10:56.406 --> 10:58.738
Blood may be spilled,
but only for show.

10:58.909 --> 11:01.742
Serious punishment will be meted out
to the man who caused them.

11:01.912 --> 11:04.028
We shall serve you
with honor, Dominus.

11:04.206 --> 11:05.992
I expect no less.

11:06.166 --> 11:07.702
Return to quarters.

11:10.671 --> 11:12.832
Spartacus, remain.

11:13.006 --> 11:14.962
What make you of Crixus?

11:15.133 --> 11:17.340
Numerius insisted upon him,
yet with his wounds barely sealed...

11:17.511 --> 11:19.126
He believes himself ready.

11:19.304 --> 11:20.840
To a fault.

11:21.014 --> 11:23.266
The ego bruises deeper
than the flesh.

11:25.477 --> 11:28.469
He brought this house
great honor not long ago.

11:28.647 --> 11:30.638
Do not overly embarrass
the man.

11:32.359 --> 11:35.567
I will give Numerius a show,
nothing more.

11:36.655 --> 11:40.193
When I put on the toga virilis,
it was in this very room,

11:40.367 --> 11:43.279
surrounded by my father's
champions.

11:43.453 --> 11:46.695
Even then I knew
that one day

11:46.874 --> 11:49.661
my own titans
would eclipse them all,

11:49.835 --> 11:52.451
none more so
than Spartacus,

11:52.629 --> 11:55.166
the bringer of rain.

11:56.216 --> 11:59.629
Eh? Ha ha!

12:00.679 --> 12:02.340
You honor me.

12:03.765 --> 12:06.222
You stand above all others.

12:06.393 --> 12:07.849
Continue on this path,

12:08.020 --> 12:10.181
and we will have the world!

12:10.355 --> 12:12.220
( roars )

12:30.042 --> 12:31.873
You have been avoiding me.

12:32.044 --> 12:34.786
l have been tending
my duties.

12:34.963 --> 12:37.249
Your manner hardens.

12:37.424 --> 12:39.881
I prefer it soft, as the moment
we shared not so long ago.

12:40.052 --> 12:44.421
You mistake smile and friendly touch
beyond intent.

12:44.598 --> 12:46.964
And the key that went missing
from my clasp

12:47.142 --> 12:49.884
after your friendly touch?

12:50.062 --> 12:55.182
It did not by mistake
draw into your palm, did it?

12:56.401 --> 12:58.392
It did not.

12:58.570 --> 13:01.812
And yet you tense
from question.

13:01.990 --> 13:05.073
Such reaction warrants
fair search.

13:05.243 --> 13:07.029
My hands service
Domina alone.

13:07.204 --> 13:08.865
She would not be pleased
to have yours

13:09.039 --> 13:12.372
laid upon me
without her consent,

13:12.542 --> 13:17.036
or to learn a guard
has misplaced his key.

13:19.132 --> 13:21.544
I would not have it so.

13:23.762 --> 13:27.846
You have a reputation
for your handling of women.

13:28.016 --> 13:30.473
Seek your loss
among them

13:30.644 --> 13:33.386
and do not press me again
with accusation.

13:45.409 --> 13:47.195
You trust llithyia
not to come unhinged

13:47.369 --> 13:48.779
in front of the magistrate?

13:48.954 --> 13:50.660
I shall keep
watchful eyes upon her.

13:50.831 --> 13:52.412
More watchful than the last,
I pray.

13:52.582 --> 13:55.619
Everything worked
to our advantage.

13:55.794 --> 13:57.955
llithyia's in our debt,
and through collection

13:58.130 --> 14:00.462
we gained access
to the most noble of families.

14:00.632 --> 14:02.543
She attends to the list?

14:02.718 --> 14:05.630
She will draw all
to the magistrate's celebration,

14:05.804 --> 14:08.796
so artfully placed
within our walls.

14:08.974 --> 14:12.762
There must be no cause
for disappointment.

14:13.937 --> 14:16.804
After the exhibition
between Spartacus and Crixus

14:16.982 --> 14:19.519
has ignited his son,

14:19.693 --> 14:21.900
I will broach the magistrate
on the subject of political office.

14:22.070 --> 14:24.026
And be well received.

14:24.197 --> 14:26.153
( guffaws )

14:26.324 --> 14:28.986
To behold Solonius's face
when he sees me

14:29.161 --> 14:32.528
consort with the highest
echelon of Capua...

14:32.706 --> 14:35.448
Solonius? And how should he
witness such a thing?

14:35.625 --> 14:38.833
By invitation.
I desire his eyes upon me

14:39.004 --> 14:41.791
when I am anointed
by the magistrate.

14:41.965 --> 14:44.001
I want him to see
that as my fortunes rise,

14:44.176 --> 14:46.667
his plummet.

14:46.845 --> 14:49.928
You taunt an injured snake,

14:50.098 --> 14:52.009
one that may yet turn
and strike.

14:52.184 --> 14:54.049
Ease your mind.

14:54.227 --> 14:57.811
The serpent's head will be struck
from its body in due course.

14:57.981 --> 15:02.315
And Solonius will never
see it coming.

15:31.848 --> 15:34.134
So you and Crixus battling
as entertainment, eh?

15:34.309 --> 15:37.221
- Something the boy will never forget.
- It is only exhibition.

15:37.395 --> 15:39.306
Dominus gave
strict instructions

15:39.481 --> 15:41.563
to avoid grievous injury.

16:06.424 --> 16:08.585
I do not believe
he was listening.

16:17.269 --> 16:19.726
Your Gaul is restored.

16:20.772 --> 16:22.888
Lucretia: He is not alone.

16:23.066 --> 16:25.557
The sun has revived
what the night had withered.

16:25.735 --> 16:28.067
Due to kindness
of a dear friend.

16:28.238 --> 16:30.650
And is that kindness
returned?

16:30.824 --> 16:32.689
The magistrate's celebration

16:32.868 --> 16:36.577
will swell
with all names provided.

16:36.746 --> 16:39.158
Gratitude.

16:39.332 --> 16:42.870
Would that I had words
to multiply it in response.

16:44.588 --> 16:46.829
Aw fuck.

16:47.007 --> 16:48.998
My finger.

16:50.010 --> 16:51.750
(laughing)

16:51.928 --> 16:54.590
Yet the value of a friend
cannot be expressed

16:54.764 --> 16:57.927
by the clever grouping
of letters.

16:58.101 --> 17:01.639
It is blood and flesh,

17:01.813 --> 17:04.520
granting life to the world.

17:13.700 --> 17:17.033
You submit like a fucking girl
begging for a cock to split her open.

17:17.204 --> 17:18.865
l was bested.
What would you have me do?

17:19.039 --> 17:20.825
Rise and fight
till your final breath

17:20.999 --> 17:22.990
or prove the name
brother false.

17:26.504 --> 17:28.995
Heard of opportunities
in Sicilia.

17:29.174 --> 17:31.506
Had I been wise, we would have
moved there to escape my debts.

17:31.676 --> 17:34.088
Yet the advice of my wife
fell short of its mark.

17:34.262 --> 17:36.218
It is a distance to travel--

17:36.389 --> 17:38.675
from a woman's mouth
to a man's ears.

17:40.852 --> 17:42.717
I shall close the gap

17:42.896 --> 17:45.262
from this point forward.

17:45.440 --> 17:49.399
Aurelia tells me Sicilia is an island
blessed by the gods.

17:49.569 --> 17:52.276
You must visit us there
when you gain freedom.

17:52.447 --> 17:55.985
| no longer concern myself
with thoughts beyond these walls.

17:56.159 --> 17:57.899
And nor should you.

17:58.078 --> 18:01.195
A true champion
dreams only of the arena.

18:03.875 --> 18:06.867
And what does one dream of
when he's no longer a champion?

18:11.675 --> 18:15.839
Regaining the title from the thief
who stole it from me.

18:16.012 --> 18:17.218
He stole nothing.

18:17.389 --> 18:19.175
If I am a thief,

18:19.349 --> 18:21.510
the crime was witnessed
by all of Capua

18:21.685 --> 18:24.722
and is still celebrated
to this day.

18:24.896 --> 18:26.807
Guard: Spartacus!

18:28.149 --> 18:30.401
You are summoned.

18:42.914 --> 18:46.031
The magistrate will arrive tomorrow,
well in advance of his guests,

18:46.209 --> 18:48.700
to ensure that preparations
are to his standards.

18:48.878 --> 18:50.254
While I reassure him,

18:50.422 --> 18:52.458
I would have you
tend the boy.

18:52.632 --> 18:55.294
lt's imperative
that he is well satisfied,

18:55.468 --> 18:58.756
and by proximity
his noble father.

18:58.930 --> 19:00.966
The name Batiatus
will be honored.

19:01.141 --> 19:03.132
And envied
throughout the republic.

19:09.607 --> 19:11.734
Spartacus:
You move unwisely.

19:12.819 --> 19:14.355
You play?

19:14.529 --> 19:16.110
I've had occasion,

19:16.281 --> 19:18.021
during my time
with the auxiliary.

19:18.199 --> 19:19.939
By all means,

19:20.118 --> 19:21.858
grace us
with your knowledge.

19:33.631 --> 19:37.715
It appears our champion
has no head for games of strategy.

19:40.138 --> 19:42.800
( chuckles )

19:42.974 --> 19:44.885
Battles may be lost,

19:45.060 --> 19:48.552
and yet the war
concludes in victory.

19:51.441 --> 19:54.353
Ah, treacherous fuck.

19:54.527 --> 19:55.858
( laughs)

19:56.029 --> 19:58.315
Played like a true Roman.

19:58.490 --> 20:00.572
Fall from your chair
and bring us some wine.

20:11.503 --> 20:14.119
The Syrian could swindle
the scales from a snake,

20:14.297 --> 20:15.707
but never command
a charge.

20:15.882 --> 20:18.965
Come, let us have
a contest between men.

20:33.149 --> 20:34.855
Oh, your touch
has been missed.

20:35.026 --> 20:39.144
And thoughts of yours
consume me.

20:39.322 --> 20:42.109
Soon you will feel
the hands of a champion

20:42.283 --> 20:44.365
once again upon you.

20:44.536 --> 20:47.027
The match with Spartacus
is but exhibition.

20:47.205 --> 20:50.413
I know the crowd as my heart.

20:50.583 --> 20:53.165
They will yearn for blood,

20:53.336 --> 20:56.248
and I shall give it to them.

20:56.423 --> 20:58.379
Dominus forbids injury.

20:58.550 --> 21:01.792
To make attempt
on Spartacus's life is to--

21:01.970 --> 21:03.301
is to risk your own.

21:03.471 --> 21:06.087
This is my life.

21:06.266 --> 21:08.598
If not champion,

21:08.768 --> 21:10.429
lam nothing.

21:12.897 --> 21:15.013
Then I must be
without my mind

21:15.191 --> 21:17.682
to love only the man.

21:17.861 --> 21:20.398
Yes.

21:20.572 --> 21:22.904
And | relish your madness.

22:06.826 --> 22:09.442
Oh, fuck the heavens.

22:09.621 --> 22:13.113
How can you keep besting a man
so far above your station?

22:14.876 --> 22:17.868
l sprung from my mother
with sword in hand.

22:18.046 --> 22:20.458
The ways of battle
are second nature,

22:20.632 --> 22:23.123
passed down
from father to son.

22:25.261 --> 22:27.297
I regret my own father
never saw

22:27.472 --> 22:30.009
the advantage
of military glory,

22:30.183 --> 22:32.799
never saw the spoils
that could be won,

22:32.977 --> 22:36.094
the patronage, the alliances forged
had he taken up arms.

22:38.066 --> 22:41.934
He aspired to be no further
than what he was--

22:42.111 --> 22:44.523
a simple lanista,

22:44.697 --> 22:46.312
far from Rome.

22:46.491 --> 22:48.698
You and I, however--

22:48.868 --> 22:51.484
we have fashioned wings
to raise us higher

22:51.663 --> 22:53.324
than the muck and mire
of heritage,

22:53.498 --> 22:56.080
higher than our fathers
could ever imagine.

22:59.003 --> 23:01.039
Quintus.

23:01.214 --> 23:03.170
What stirs such a vision
from her dreams?

23:03.341 --> 23:06.629
My husband
not beside me.

23:06.803 --> 23:09.590
Spartacus was helping me
hone my game.

23:09.764 --> 23:12.506
Over a cup of wine?

23:12.684 --> 23:15.346
( chuckles )

23:17.855 --> 23:19.982
Gratitude for the instruction.

23:24.862 --> 23:27.524
Have your senses flown,

23:27.699 --> 23:29.564
to share drink with a slave?

23:29.742 --> 23:32.119
| drink with the champion
of Capua.

23:32.287 --> 23:33.868
Crixus was a champion,

23:34.038 --> 23:36.324
yet no cup was ever raised
with him.

23:36.499 --> 23:38.706
Crixus is a brute.

23:38.876 --> 23:40.741
